data.description:
Templating isn't that hard if you put your mind to it. Write a function that will compile any code (in the form of a string or function), turning any marked text into a regular string, then running the code and returning the result (a function should become a function, a string will become whatever the expression returns). Text is marked as a "literal" by starting with the characters `_/*` and ending with `*/`.

(Don't worry about closures and whatnot with the functions.)

```javascript
compile("_/* string \"with\" 'quotes' and \\ slashes */") === "string \"with\" 'quotes' and \\ slashes ";

compile(function(url, text) {
  return _/*<tag>
    <a href="*/ + url + _/*">*/ + text + _/* \ (new window)</a>
  </tag>*/;
})("http://www.google.com/", "Google") === "<tag>\n    <a href=\"http://www.google.com/\">Google \\ (new window)</a>\n  </tag>";
```

See how few lines you can manage to write a fully-working template compiler in without using any libraries whatsoever!
